{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"a5y34zgjcq1ci23zez4v7hn","title":"WAI-ARIA","desc":"Notes on WAI-ARIA","updated":1652423840872,"created":1652423755483,"custom":{},"fname":"devnotes.a11y.wai-aria","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"b73497e26356a252aaaca4fdd5d25d4a","links":[],"anchors":{"general-info":{"type":"header","text":"General Info","value":"general-info","line":7,"column":0,"depth":2},"5-rules-of-aria":{"type":"header","text":"5 Rules of ARIA","value":"5-rules-of-aria","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"eM4JZQZat4r1vRHaWLGrd","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"wai-aria\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#wai-aria\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>WAI-ARIA</h1>\n<h2 id=\"general-info\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#general-info\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>General Info</h2>\n<p>Web Accessibility Initiativeâ€™s Accessible Rich Internet Applications specification. The purpose of WAI-ARIA (often referred to as just ARIA) is to define a way to make web content more accessible when native HTML is unable to do so. Think of ARIA as something that fills in the accessible gaps left by native HTML.</p>\n<h2 id=\"5-rules-of-aria\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#5-rules-of-aria\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>5 Rules of ARIA</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Always use native HTML elements and attributes over ARIA when possible.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Never change native semantics, unless you have no other choice.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>All interactive ARIA controls must be usable with a keyboard.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Never use role='presentation' or aria-hidden='true' on focusable elements.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>All interactive elements must have an accessible name.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>","noteInd